{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"176a8403-e2b9-4013-a04a-18aacf0f8ead","content":"Two things change when moving to xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe old VSTest filter:\n```\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nbecomes the MTP `--filter` expression:\n```\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Trait[Category]=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`and`** (logical operators are words: `and`, `or`, `not`)\n- **`Category=Smoke`** → **`Trait[Category]=Smoke`** — MTP doesn't have a built-in `Category` property; traits are accessed via `Trait[<name>]`\n\n### 2. Trait attribute\n\nxUnit v3 dropped the `[Trait]` attribute in favor of strongly-typed category attributes. Replace:\n\n```csharp\n// v2\n[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n```\n\nwith the built-in:\n\n```csharp\n// v3\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]\n```\n\n(`[Category]` ships in `xunit.v3` — no extra package needed.)\n\nYour full CI command becomes:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Trait[Category]=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e056d2b-de13-49ca-aabc-606f610f3097","outputTokens":322},"id":"44ecb2ac-1d28-424c-87ec-22ef63934cda","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:50:47.788Z","parentId":"c9d7ea82-0fe9-4502-9e19-57b470fe77fe"}
